## Cancelling Jobs
Below is an example of cancelling a job based on its job ID.

```javascript
const myJobId = 1;
const job = new client.job(myJobId);
const force = false; // Do not force cancel.

// Cancel Job
job.cancel(force).then(() => {
  console.log('Cancel has been successfully requested.');
}).catch((err) => {
  // Display error.
});
```

